{It’s been 20 years since I co-authored my first book, Chess Openings for Black, Explained (first published in 2005) . It was an incredible journey that began with me meeting my coach, legendary GM Roman Dzindzichashvili, a renowned theoretician and a former top 10 player in the world. Together, Roman and I teamed up with 3-time US Champion, GM Lev Alburt, to present a complete repertoire to the wider audience of chess players of all levels (Chess Openings For White, Explained was published later). The ideas and the presentation with colorful text, vivid diagrams and the original concept of Memory Markers really appealed to everyone and it became an instant best seller!  Now, I am happy to bring the repertoire for Black to Chessable, continuing the journey on this platform, where I love interacting with Chessable users. Of course, the theory progressed “just a bit” over the last 20 years and many chapters of this book needed some serious updating. However, the core openings and our recommendations are still sound to this day, and I am happy to present them with modern engine updates. In this course, I will give you a complete Lifetime Repertoire against all of White’s options except e4 . For e4 , I recommend visiting my fresh and updated  Hyper-Accelerated Dragon Lifetime Repertoire course   The main recommendations are as follows:    Against 1. d4 , we play the Nimzo-Indian and Bogo-Indian   Against 1. c4 and 1. Nf3 , we play 1... c5 with Symmetrical English   All other openings are covered in detail and include the trendy London System, Jobava-London, Trompowsky, Torre Attack and many others.   This repertoire centers on the Dark Square strategy, which involves controlling key dark squares with our pawns and pieces. As a result, many of the lines we will explore are interconnected, all stemming from this core principle of dark-square control. Furthermore, I have dedicated an entire chapter to typical pawn structures that commonly arise from the Nimzo-Indian and Bogo-Indian openings. I believe this feature is unique to this course on the Chessable platform. I specifically chose variations that emphasize the Dark Square strategy, and I hope you will find the material both easy and fun to learn!  This course is geared toward all levels of chess players, and I believe the strategic themes are easy to grasp due to their common ideas. I have played this repertoire myself. In fact, within a year of writing the original Black Book, I achieved the Grandmaster title in 2006! I have also been teaching these openings to my students for 20 years, and many of them quickly climbed the ranks of club players using this repertoire. Some even became Masters. Therefore, I am confident that this course will benefit all Chessable users.  This is my 4th Chessable course, and it's packed with more verbal explanations than ever before! I hope the material is instructive, fun, and easy to learn. I look forward to seeing many victories posted on the Discussion board by you, the dear readers!  Best,  Eugene} 1. Z0 *

