s Naijer and Esipenko still wheel it out once in a while.}) 5. a3 {This is a tricky move as White forces our hand in order to recapture on d2 with the queen.} Bxd2+ 6. Qxd2 {Now, White wants to get a dream center with Nc3 & e4 .} d6 {We follow up with our standard plan of ... d6 & ... e5 .} 7. Nc3 e5 8. dxe5 dxe5 9. e3 {This passive approach gives us an easy game:} O-O 10. Be2 Rd8 11. Qc2 e4 {Black takes over the center!} 12. Nd4 c5 ({White's poor knight has to drop to b3 since Ndb5? is met by} 12... a6 $1 {Black's pawns dominate the center.}) *

