[White "1) Bogo: 4.Bd2 - Early Fianchetto & Sidelines"]
[Black "Conclusion: 4.Bd2 & 6.Bg2 lines"]
[Result "*"]
[PlyCount "1"]
[GameId "2176748629308139"]

{Conclusion: In the 4.Bd2 & 6.Bg2 Bogo-Indian lines, it's important to remember the idea of taking on d2 with Bxd2+! . The point is that if White takes back with the queen, they run into issues after ... Ne4 ! All of a sudden, they may lose a d-pawn or have their pawns doubled. Stronger players know to recapture on d2 with the knight ( Nbxd2 ) but in this case, we execute the key strategic idea with ... d6 & ... e5 !   The resulting middlegames are quite complex and often lead to a maneuvering game. Remember some key ideas: the ... Nb8 - a6 regrouping, a timely ... c6 push, and how to deal with White's kingside expansion. This opening is based on a rock-solid strategic foundation and the ideas will help your general chess understanding as well!} 1. Z0 *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
