d6 ({Here, White chooses between an aggressive} 9... d5 {or a simple} 10. O-O {.}) 10. O-O {White goes for a simple development plan.} e5 {We execute the main idea of our setup: building a beautiful c7 - d6 - e5 pawn chain that points directly at White's king.} ({I believe it's slightly more accurate than the original book recommendation of} 10... Nxc3 11. Rxc3 e5 {since White has the extra option of .}) 11. dxe5 dxe5 {This gives us a central pawn on e5 with easy play.} 12. Qc2 Nxc3 (12... f5 $5 {is also interesting.}) 13. Qxc3 Bg4 {This is a comfortable position for Black as we have completed development, we control the center with a nice e5 -pawn and are about to fight for the open file with ... Rfd8 or ... Rad8 next.} *

