s is the main line.} O-O 9. Bg2 d6 ({Here, White chooses between an aggressive} 9... d5 {or a simple} 10. O-O {.}) 10. d5 Nb8 {These days I like this over the original recommendation of ... Nxc3 since I believe the knight on e4 limits White's options.} (10... Nxc3 11. Rxc3 Nb8 12. dxe6 fxe6 {allows} 13. Re3 $1 {which is a bit annoying, for example:} e5 14. O-O Nc6 15. Nd4 $1 {with an edge for White.}) 11. O-O e5 12. Nd2 Nxc3 *

