ct with our b7 -bishop to checkmate White's king. Of course, White has plenty of defensive resources, but remember, it's always easier to attack than to defend!} f5 {We launch our attack!} 13. Rfd1 {This is a logical build-up move. White wants to prepare d5 and reserves c1 for the other rook.} Rf6 {We don't mind d5 and transfer our rook to h6 .} 14. d5 Rh6 15. dxe6 Ndc5 {Black is ready to win back the pawn with ... Nxe6 .} ({Or} 15... Nf8 {with the same idea.}) 16. b4 {This is a human move, why not kick the knight.} Nxe6 {We've reached a very complex position. I believe that it's easier to play with Black as we are attacking. Of course, White is fine with the best defense, but good luck defending in a practical game.} 17. Rd5 {A nice idea, but we don't take the gift.} Qe8 18. Rxf5 Qg6 19. Rd5 {White has to find this only move not to be worse.} c6 20. Rdd1 Rf8 {All of our major pieces are aimed at the king. I don't care about the engine's 0.0 eval and would take Black in a heartbeat!} *

