ct with our b7 -bishop to checkmate White's king. Of course, White has plenty of defensive resources, but remember, it's always easier to attack than to defend!} f5 {We launch our attack!} 13. Rad1 {This rook move is better as f1 -rook is an important defender against the attack. White wants to push d5 next.} Rf6 {Our reaction is the same, regardless which rook moves to d1 .} 14. d5 Rh6 15. dxe6 Ndc5 (15... Nf8 {also works. We will take the e6 -pawn next.}) 16. Rd5 {This is the best try for advantage. Make sure not to take the rook!} Nxe6 {We follow through with our attacking mindset and don't take the rook.} 17. Rxf5 Qe8 {The position is extremely complex but I believe in Black's attack. The queen is ready to join the attack with ... Qg6 next.} 18. Nd4 Nxd4 19. exd4 Qg6 20. Rf3 {Now we have a spectacular idea.} Ng3 ({A truly picturesque move. White has to play only moves to not lose. Bd3! The only move.} 20... Qh5 21. h3 $1 {Again, only move! Nxf1} d5 $1 22. Rf8+ $1 Rxf8 {Kxf8 Bf5 Qe8 Kxf1 Bc8 The engine of course claims 0.0, but let's be realistic, your opponent won't survive this long.}) *

