{Conclusion: While 4.Nbd2 lines are not so popular, you still have to know how to fight White's two bishops after the eventual a3 . Most games see White take back with the queen and get ready to develop slowly with e3 , Be2 , and O-O followed by b3 / b4 and Bb2 .    In this case, it's important to know the right plan: we play ... Ne4 and ... f5 and get ready to attack White's king. Keep the center closed, and learn when to launch an attack with ... Rf6 , or when to slow down and play ... Qe7 and ... c6 .   If White goes for an early b4 , remember the cool idea of playing ... a5 and meeting b5 with the novel plan of castling queenside!} 1. Z0 *

