ot pin a knight and develop the bishop at the same time? But this is exactly what we want!} h6 {Asking the bishop its intentions. We hope for the autopilot response Bh4 to spring our trap!} 7. Bh4 {White's most logical and most played move, which turns out to be a mistake already! By the way, this move has appeared in over 7,000 online blitz games and has been played 68% of the time in this position!} g5 {Now, we get to uncork our trap!} 8. Bg3 ({The sacrifice on g5 doesn't work: after} 8. Nxg5 $2 hxg5 9. Bxg5 {, Black wins with pretty much any logical move, but} Nxd4 {is easiest.}) 8... g4 {And just like that, White will lost a key central pawn. The engine gives -1 already!} 9. Nd2 Nxd4 {We grab the free central pawn while attacking the queen, but our trap is not fully complete as you will see shortly.} 10. Qa4+ {White gets giddy with joy, thinking they win a piece with this double attack, but...} Bd7 {Make sure to play this move with a poker face, or perhaps even shake your head in disgust as though you just blundered a piece...} 11. Qd1 {This move keeps the game going, but with an engine eval of -2.6 already, Black will have all the fun. Let me know you one typical line:} Bc6 {Activating the bishop.} 12. e3 Bxc3 {I like to insert this trade to ruin White's pawns.} 13. bxc3 Nf5 {Black has the extra pawn, better development and a superior pawn structure! We have many good plans such as ... Qe7 and castle queenside and launch the pawn storm with ... h5 & ... h4 next.} *

