ot pin a knight and develop the bishop at the same time? But this is exactly what we want!} h6 {Asking the bishop its intentions. We hope for the autopilot response Bh4 to spring our trap!} 7. Bh4 {White's most logical and most played move, which turns out to be a mistake already! By the way, this move has appeared in over 7,000 online blitz games and has been played 68% of the time in this position!} g5 {Now, we get to uncork our trap!} 8. Bg3 ({The sacrifice on g5 doesn't work: after} 8. Nxg5 $2 hxg5 9. Bxg5 {, Black wins with pretty much any logical move, but} Nxd4 {is easiest.}) 8... g4 {And just like that, White will lost a key central pawn. The engine gives -1 already!} 9. Nd2 Nxd4 {We grab the free central pawn while attacking the queen, but our trap is not fully complete as you will see shortly.} 10. Qa4+ {White gets giddy with joy, thinking they win a piece with this double attack, but...} Bd7 {Make sure to play this move with a poker face, or perhaps even shake your head in disgust as though you just blundered a piece...} 11. Qxb4 {An unfortunate, game ending blunder for our opponent.} Nc2+ {The family forks completes our trap and triggers immediate resignation from White. When your opponent shakes your hand, remember to mention that you knew all of this from a Chessable course! Many of my students won games like this, and now it's time for you to celebrate winning a nice miniature as well!} *

