[GameId "2176748629545801"]

{Conclusion: The Classical Variation 4.Qc2 is the most common line at all levels. However, we get to surprise our opponent with the rare 4...Nc6 . Many people fall for a well-known trap after Nf3 d6 Bg5 h6 Bh4 g5! Bg3 g4! We will win the pawn on d4 and enjoy a large edge.  Strong players who are aware of the trap will play Bd2 followed by a3 to get the bishop pair. However, Black's advantage in development and the key strategic idea to play for ... e5 give us excellent counterplay. For example: O-O a3 Bxc3 Bxc3 Re8 e3 e5 with a complex fight ahead.} 1. Z0 *

