hite is about to get the bishop pair, which is a long-term asset. Thus, we need to get our counterplay going quickly.} 6. Ng3 {This is a more ambitious plan as White doesn't mind doubling their pawns after ... Bxc3 + bxc3 .} Bxc3+ {We take the opportunity to weaken White's pawn structure.} 7. bxc3 d5 {Black doesn't mind eliminating White's doubled pawn as long as the light-squared bishops are traded.} 8. cxd5 {This was tried by Hikaru in the Armageddon game vs Fabi, but Black is too solid.} Bxf1 9. Rxf1 Qxd5 {The most accurate way to recapture, hitting the g2 -pawn and keeping both the ... e5 and ... c5 options to undermine White's center.} 10. f3 Nc6 ({While there's nothing wrong with} 10... c5 {, I believe developing the knight gives Black better chances.}) 11. e4 Qc4 {Taking over the light squares and targeting the c3 -pawn.} 12. Bd2 O-O-O {I like this aggressive option the best. We can now launch the kingside storm with ... h5 & ... h4 while it's unclear what White should do with his king.} ({There's nothing wrong with} 12... O-O {either, going for a more positional game.}) *

