hite is about to get the bishop pair, which is a long-term asset. Thus, we need to get our counterplay going quickly.} 6. Ng3 {This is a more ambitious plan as White doesn't mind doubling their pawns after ... Bxc3 + bxc3 .} Bxc3+ {We take the opportunity to weaken White's pawn structure.} 7. bxc3 d5 {Black doesn't mind eliminating White's doubled pawn as long as the light-squared bishops are traded.} 8. cxd5 {This was tried by Hikaru in the Armageddon game vs Fabi, but Black is too solid.} Bxf1 9. Nxf1 {This was recommended by GM Swiercz, but Black is doing fine here as well.} Qxd5 10. f3 c5 {We strike the center!} 11. e4 Qd7 12. Ne3 O-O 13. O-O Rd8 14. Bb2 Nc6 {We attack White's strong d4 -pawn, forcing them to make concessions. Black has great counterplay.} *

