hite is about to get the bishop pair, which is a long-term asset. Thus, we need to get our counterplay going quickly.} 6. Ng3 {This is a more ambitious plan as White doesn't mind doubling their pawns after ... Bxc3 + bxc3 .} Bxc3+ {We take the opportunity to weaken White's pawn structure.} 7. bxc3 d5 {Black doesn't mind eliminating White's doubled pawn as long as the light-squared bishops are traded.} 8. Qa4+ {This allows Black to get a comfortable endgame:} Qd7 9. Qxd7+ Nbxd7 10. cxd5 Bxf1 11. Kxf1 exd5 {We will castle long and try to put pressure on White with ... h5 & ... h4 next.} *

