xg2 {We are brave and take the pawn!} 7. Rg1 Bf3 {The most precise. Now, White has to deal with two pins!} 8. Qc2 {White sidesteps the pin while taking control over e4 , preparing Rg3 next.} Nc6 {The most precise! We don't care about the g7 -pawn and go for rapid development.} 9. a3 Bxc3+ ({The simplest, but} 9... Bd6 $5 {is good as well.}) 10. Nxc3 (10. bxc3 Nh5 $1 {and ... Qh4 next.}) 10... Nh5 ({I will overrule the engine on this one, as it claims} 10... O-O {is better, but I prefer to activate my queen to h4 first.}) 11. b4 Qh4 12. Bb2 Qxh2 {Why not grab another pawn?} 13. Rf1 f5 {Restricting White's battery and getting ready to castle short.} 14. Ne2 {White is ready to castle long now.} O-O 15. O-O-O Ne7 {The position remains complex, but our bishop and queen eyeing g2 totally paralyze White. I don't really see how they can generate any attack. The engine agrees and gives us a -2.5 advantage!} *

