referred choice, as I believe it fits our general strategy of establishing a clear pawn weakness and attacking it next.} 8. bxc3 {Now, White's pawn structure is ruined, but it's not easy to attack it yet. Therefore, we continue with normal development.} c5 {We apply the well-known positional motif of 'fixing' the double pawns, i.e., blocking them with our pawn to make them immobile.  White's main plan is to prepare e4 , which they can do with Nd2 , Qe2 , or Re1 . We will examine all of these options.} 9. Nd2 {White's main idea is to play for e4 and mobilize their center.} Nc6 {We develop and apply extra pressure on the d-pawn. Now, White can either overprotect the d-pawn with Nb3 or Bb2 , or sacrifice a pawn with e4!? .} 10. e4 {This is White's most ambitious option, but not without its risks, since they give up the central pawn.} cxd4 11. cxd4 Nxd4 {The most principled approach. We ask White to demonstrate their compensation for the central pawn.} 12. e5 {The most direct, opening up their bishop with tempo and hitting our knight.} ({Please note that slow moves like} 12. Bb2 {are met with} e5 $1) 12... Ne8 {The only move, but solid. Now, time is of the essence. Can White create some threats before their initiative fizzles out?} 13. Qg4 {I believe this is White's strongest move and requires accurate defense from Black.} Nc6 {We must retreat for now, but at the same time, we attack the e5 -pawn.} 14. Nf3 {A logical move, White is opening up the c1 -bishop.} f5 {The same star move that gave us great play against 13.Qh5 works here as well!} 15. Qg3 {White should not take en passant to keep our e8 -knight passive.} Nc7 {Black managed to stabilize the position and the knight is heading to a6 and c5 next.} ({Please note that White can't pose direct threats, as Bh6 is met with the simple} 15... Qe7 $1 {The attack comes to a screeching halt.}) 16. Ba3 Ne7 ({Or} 16... Re8 {first and then ... Ne7 .}) 17. Ng5 h6 18. Nh3 Na6 19. Nf4 Nc5 20. Nh5 Rf7 {Black has once again stopped White's threats, and with a superior knight on c5 and a bishop on b7 , we will eventually aim to convert the extra pawn.} *

