{The Classical Setup by White with 5.Bd3 & 6.Nf3 is best met with normal development with ... Bb7 & ... O-O . However, the moment White castles, we take on c3 and define the pawn structure. Remember to play an early c5! to fix White's pawns. White's main idea is to play for e4 . If they go Re1 or Qe2 , we execute a standard blockade with Ne4! If White goes for Nd2 , we play Nc6! and the game revolves around the center. Against Bb2 , we can't stop e4 anymore, and resort to the standard blocking idea of d6 and e4 e5 , setting up the famous Huebner Wall!} 1. Z0 *

