[GameId "2176748629701533"]

{The Sämisch Variation gives us an easy target, the pawn on c4 . Thus, our plan is to quickly attack it with a simple plan of ... b6 , ... Na6 , ... Ba6 and ... Na5 . White has several plans to fight for the initiative. Remember to meet Bg5 with h6 Bh4 Qc8! From there, after ... Na5 , the queen can be transferred to c6 via b7 , attacking the c4 -pawn. If White chooses a calm approach with Bd3 , we insert Na5 Qe2 and play a useful waiting move . The point is to activate the queen via ... d7 , preparing to castle long or go ... Qa4 . If White plays f4 , we answer with d5! exd5 Qe7!! , anticipating the queen trade and winning the c4 -pawn in the ensuring endgame. Overall, this is a fun line to face, as White is often one mistake away from getting into trouble!} 1. Z0 *

