1. d4 Nf6 {We develop our knight first and take control over the vital e4 -square. The underlining theme of my course is to fight for the center with the pieces.} 2. c4 e6 {We are getting ready to develop our bishop to b4 against both Nc3 and Nf3 .} 3. Nc3 {The starting position of the Nimzo-Indian Defense. White develops the knight behind the c-pawn to its most natural square, and takes more control of the e4 -square. This can lead to more sharp variations than the Bogo-Indian.} Bb4 4. f3 {This line was very popular in the 1990s and was chosen by many attacking players, such as the young Alexei Shirov. White tries to improve on the Saemisch Variation without losing the tempo with 3.a3 and aims to take over the center with d5 next.} d5 {We stop White's plan as soon as possible. Please note that it is rare for us to move our d-pawn this early in this opening. Thus, the structure arising from these lines is not typical of the Nimzo, and you have to be precise early on!} {Now, since White can't easily play e4 , opening up the game with cxd5 exd5 is not recommended as the knight on g1 gets stranded.} 5. a3 {White's best move! Now that we have committed our d-pawn to d5 , White doesn't mind if we take on c3 , as they will undouble their pawns next.} Be7 {We have to be precise! Taking on c3 only helps White, as they will strengthen their center, undouble their pawns, and maintain the bishop pair.} 6. e4 {White achieves their plan, but we have a little surprise for them!} dxe4 7. fxe4 e5 ({I like this idea recommended in the original book, even though these days} 7... c5 {is much more popular at the top level. This is actually good news since your opponent will not expect it!  Black forces White to weaken dark-squares by playing} 8. d5 {, otherwise White's center will be destroyed.}) 8. dxe5 {This greedy pawn grab cannot be recommended, as Black gets easy targets.} Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 {White has lost the right to castle, but taking back with knight would've dropped the e4 -pawn.} Ng4 {With a dual threat of ... Nf2 + fork and ... Nxe5 , we will get our pawn back and enjoy a nice edge, since White has a weak pawn on e4 and has lost the right to castle.} *

