1. d4 Nf6 {We develop our knight first and take control over the vital e4 -square. The underlining theme of my course is to fight for the center with the pieces.} 2. c4 e6 {We are getting ready to develop our bishop to b4 against both Nc3 and Nf3 .} 3. Nc3 {The starting position of the Nimzo-Indian Defense. White develops the knight behind the c-pawn to its most natural square, and takes more control of the e4 -square. This can lead to more sharp variations than the Bogo-Indian.} Bb4 4. Bg5 {This is the Leningrad Variation. White answers a pin with a pin, hoping to induce ... h6 and ... g5 to take advantage of Black's weakened kingside. These days, it's a rare guest at tournaments for all levels.} c5 ({This is more accurate than} 4... h6 {as there are lines where the bishop on g5 will be attacked via our queen on a5 .}) 5. d5 {This is White's most common move.} Bxc3+ {We take the opportunity to ruin White's pawn structure.} {If we start with first, this would give White an option to defend the knight with Rc1 .} 6. bxc3 d6 ({Please note that} 6... h6 7. Bh4 d6 {will transpose.}) 7. e3 h6 {A useful intermezzo to push the bishop to h4 .} 8. Bh4 e5 {We've achieved a dream setup in the Nimzo known as the Huebner Wall. Please note that White's pawn is on e3 here, which is a better version for Black! That's the reason why top GMs stopped playing this setup as White. Let's take a look at how the game may continue:} 9. f3 {This idea was tried by none other than a former World Championship Candidate GM Jan Timman vs my coach, GM Roman Dzindzi back in 1977.} g5 ({This is even stronger than Dzindzi's} 9... Bf5 {.}) 10. Bf2 e4 {We stop White from playing e4 .} 11. h4 g4 {We are locking up the kingside, taking away any breathing space from White's bishops.} 12. h5 {With idea to renew the pin with Bh4 .} exf3 13. gxf3 Qa5 {Reminding White that they also have a problem on the other flank.} 14. Qc2 Bf5 {Using a simple tactic to develop with a tempo.} 15. e4 Bh7 {We will follow up with ... Nbd7 & ... Ne5 next, White's position is on the verge of total collapse. The engine already gives -1.9 advantage!} *

