{The Leningrad Variation Bg5 is met with a central c5! push. White has to be careful to avoid tactics after e3? Qa5! Instead, d5 is their best try, but Black often gets a dream position after exchanging on c3 , and plays the ... d6 ... h6 & ... e5 Huebner Wall setup.   Remember the cool kingside expansion ideas with ... g5 & ... e4 and especially bringing the king to c7 where it's ideally placed for the action on the kingside. Our knight usually gets to e5 with total domination in the middlegame.} 1. Z0 *

