1. d4 Nf6 {We develop our knight first and take control over the vital e4 -square. The underlining theme of my course is to fight for the center with the pieces.} 2. c4 e6 {We are getting ready to develop our bishop to b4 against both Nc3 and Nf3 .} 3. Nc3 {The starting position of the Nimzo-Indian Defense. White develops the knight behind the c-pawn to its most natural square, and takes more control of the e4 -square. This can lead to more sharp variations than the Bogo-Indian.} Bb4 4. g3 {White goes for the immediate fianchetto of their light-squared bishop. This is called the Romanishin Variation, named after the Ukrainian GM Oleg Romanishin.} (4. Nf3 c5 5. g3 {is another common transposition to our setup.}) 4... c5 {We answer with an attack in the center!} 5. Nf3 Ne4 {White's slow play enables us to put more pressure on the pinned c3 -knight. Now, the most common response is to cover the knight with either Qd3 or Qc2 when our reaction will be the same in both cases: we trade on d4 and play ... Qa5 next.} 6. Qd3 cxd4 7. Nxd4 Qa5 {We add another attack on the c3 -knight.} 8. Nb3 {This is the most principled move, now we enter some fun tactics that you should try to learn and remember well!} Nxc3 {The key move, offering White a free queen...} 9. Bd2 {This is considered best according to theory.} Ne4 {Another important knight jump to remember!} 10. Qxe4 (10. Nxa5 Bxd2+ 11. Qxd2 Nxd2 12. Kxd2 {transposes to a line we looked at earlier.}) 10... Bxd2+ 11. Nxd2 {The forcing play is over and let's pause and examine the position. White still has to make 3 moves to castle: Bg2 , Qe3 , and O-O . This gives us plenty of time to castle and take over the center!} O-O 12. Bg2 Nc6 13. Qe3 d5 {Black takes over the center and wants to play ... d4 next.} 14. cxd5 exd5 15. O-O {Please note that Black's IQP is not a weakness here as White doesn't have enough time to regroup and blockade it with the knight. Our pieces are coming in with tempi.} d4 16. Qd3 Bf5 {We keep on attacking while it's hard for White to find safe haven for the queen.} *

