{The Romanishin System with a g3 fianchetto is a bit slow and it allows Black quick counterplay against White's center with c5! Nf3 Ne4! Please note that after a timely ... cxd4 & ... Qa5 ! it is White who has to be careful to avoid walking into all sorts of discovery tactics. The only somewhat dangerous line for us is Qc2 cxd4 Nxd4 Qa5 Bg2 with a piece sacrifice, but just like in the game Carlsen-Caruana, as long as you know the defensive ideas such as Nd4! and d6! , Black is doing great.} 1. Z0 *

