{White's Bd2 setup is totally harmless for Black. The easy solution is to strike the center first with c5! In most positions we get easy development and nice pressure on the center such as the good version of IQP.  If White goes for an early a3 then remember to take with Bxc3 and follow up Bxc3 with Ne4! Black gets rid of White's bishop and enjoys fast development.} 1. Z0 *

