etreating square for the knight. We aim to play on the kingside with ... Ng6 where the knight will cover the vital f4 -square.} 10. Nd2 {White typically reroutes the knight to e3 via f1 , not wasting any time on castling.} h6 {A useful waiting move.} 11. O-O Ng6 12. Re1 {Here we can be aggressive.} Nf4 13. Bf1 g5 {Black will launch the kingside attack. Note that our king is totally safe with a blocked center.} *

