1. d4 Nf6 {We develop our knight first and take control over the vital e4 -square. The underlining theme of my course is to fight for the center with the pieces.} 2. c4 e6 {We are getting ready to develop our bishop to b4 against both Nc3 and Nf3 .} 3. Nc3 {The starting position of the Nimzo-Indian Defense. White develops the knight behind the c-pawn to its most natural square, and takes more control of the e4 -square. This can lead to more sharp variations than the Bogo-Indian.} Bb4 4. Qb3 {This is called the Spielmann Variation, named after the famous chess player Rudolf Spielmann, known as the last master of the romantic school of chess.   This is an extremely rare setup for White, being only the 9th most played move in this position. White is attacking our bishop directly and tries to provoke us to take on c3 .} c5 ({I like this direct way of undermining White's center, however, you can also play the same way as against Qc2 with} 4... Nc6 {here.}) 5. dxc5 {This is White's most common move. It's quite a serious concession to trade the center pawn for a side pawn.} Nc6 {The c5 -pawn is not going anywhere, and we continue with simple development moves.} 6. Nf3 Ne4 {Another bonus for Black since White doesn't have a queen on c2 .} 7. Bd2 Nxd2 {This is a favorable trade for Black as we now get the bishop pair.} 8. Nxd2 O-O 9. g3 {White hopes that control of the long diagonal would compensation for the bishop pair, but it's not enough.} Bxc5 10. Bg2 b6 {Simple chess. White can't stop us from playing ... Bb7 next, completely neutralizing their LSB.} 11. O-O Bb7 {It's clear that White's queen to b3 sortie didn't achieve any benefits. In the meantime, Black has the bishop pair and no weaknesses.} ({The game may continue: Rac1} 11... Rb8 12. Rfd1 f5 $5 {I like this ambitious space-grabbing move. We also take away the e4 -square from White.} 13. Qc2 Qe8 {The queen is getting transferred to h5 for an attack.} 14. a3 a5 {We stopped b4 and have a simple plan of attacking White with ... Qh5 and ... f4 next. I prefer Black.}) *

