1. d4 Nf6 {We develop our knight first and take control over the vital e4 -square. The underlining theme of my course is to fight for the center with the pieces.} 2. c4 e6 {We are getting ready to develop our bishop to b4 against both Nc3 and Nf3 .} 3. g4 {This gambit was first introduced on the big stage by the ever-innovative Azeri GM Mamedyarov against Esipenko in 2022. These days, even Caruana has played it, but only in blitz!} d5 {We don't care about the pawn and strike in the center! Remember, flank attacks are best countered by central play.} 4. g5 ({After} 4. cxd5 exd5 5. g5 Ne4 {, Black is clearly better, with threats of ... Nxg5 & ... Bb4 +.}) 4... Ne4 {Our knight is very active on e4 now. We attack g5 and get ready to play ... Bb4 +.} 5. f3 {This loses on the spot.} Bb4+ 6. Nd2 (6. Bd2 {is met by} Qxg5 {.}) 6... Qxg5 7. fxe4 Qh4# {Oops!} *

