1. d4 Nf6 {We develop our knight first and take control over the vital e4 -square. The underlining theme of my course is to fight for the center with the pieces.} 2. c4 e6 {We are getting ready to develop our bishop to b4 against both Nc3 and Nf3 .} 3. Bg5 {This is called the Seirawan Attack. Recently, Grischuk has played it exclusively in blitz, and now Erigaisi picked it up. I don't know what the appeal is as it's just a bad line!} h6 {A good idea to push the bishop back to h4 .} 4. Bh4 {Taking on f6 makes no sense, as Black gets the bishop pair for free.} g5 {We keep chasing the bishop.} 5. Bg3 h5 {Now, the threat of ... h4 & ... d6 is real, we are about to win the bishop pair.} 6. Nc3 h4 7. Be5 d6 8. Bxf6 Qxf6 {Black is clearly better due to the bishop pair.} *

