{White's attempt at the Pseudo-Catalan g3 is best neutralized by the active b5! push. We take away the c4 -square and get ready to challenge their LSB with ... Bb7 . Normally, Black continues with logical ... c5 & ... Be7 development.  Remember, against the solid play of c3 to put the knight on a6 ! White's a4 is best met with b4 . If White goes for an early Bg5 & Bxf6 idea as recommended in Keep It Simple 1. d4 course then we surprise them with Nc6! offering the b5 -pawn. We get excellent compensation and White has to be careful to avoid their knight getting trapped.} 1. Z0 *

