{Conclusion: The London System is very popular at all levels these days. However, in this chapter I showed you a very rare setup based on 3... c5 and Be7!? The point is of course to prepare ... Nh5 to win the bishop pair. Most players who play c3 allow this idea and Black gets a dream version of the Classic London after ... Nc6 & ... d5 and the eventual trade of the knight for the g3 -bishop. If White is careful and prevents this trade with h3 then we go for the simple O-O and ... b6 in order to play ... Ba6 !   Remember this key idea to trade the light-squared bishops and take the sting out of the London System!} 1. Z0 *

