it is totally safe!} c4 {Black launches the attack on the enemy king!} 12. Qd2 b5 {I already prefer Black as our attack plays itself, just push the pawns and open up White's king. Here's one possible line:} 13. g5 Nh5 {Our knight helps cement the kingside.} 14. e4 {White strikes in the center, but our attack comes first!} b4 {This is most direct and best.} 15. Na4 c3 {An instructive moment, we don't care about pawns as we pry open the enemy king.} 16. Qe3 {This is White's best.} Nxf4 {The simplest.} 17. Qxf4 Bd6 {A nice tempo, trying to induce e5 .} 18. e5 cxb2+ {Another intermezzo.} 19. Nxb2 Be7 ({The dust has settled a bit but White is on the precipice as they only have one move to keep the game alive with} 19... g6 $1) 20. g6 {This is White's best and only move.} O-O {A cool-head solution, the rook enters the fight while our king is quite safe.} 21. gxf7+ Rxf7 22. Qg4 Qa5 {We don't care about the e6 -pawn and start the attack.} 23. Qxe6 {This loses, but first we need to save our knight with a nice intermezzo.} Nd8 24. Qg4 Qxa2 {It's clear that our attack is faster, the engine already gives -4 advantage here!} *

