{While the Jobava London is a trendy and popular opening, Black has a simple plan to neutralize White's ideas with 3... a6! and Bf5 , followed by ... e6 .   Don't be afraid of the early kingside expansion with f3 , g4 , & h4 as our ... h6 ! secures the safe retreat of the bishop to h7 . The main idea to remember is to not worry about kingside development and go for a rapid ... c5 , ... Nc6 and ... c4 ! and attack when White castles long. If White goes for quick Nf3 & Ne5 jump then we play a natural plan of ... e6 and ... Bb4 . Remember to meet GM Hans Niemann's g4!? idea with a temporary piece sacrifice Nxg4! The key there is to follow up with ... h5 and ... g5 . Black gets their piece back, and I showed you excellent counterplay ideas there. Finally, the totally harmless Bd3 is met with Bg6! The bishop is rock solid on g6 , and we will play for the standard ... c5 push next.} 1. Z0 *

