1. Z0 ({The Trompowsky Attack is met with c5! We don't mind allowing White to take on f6 after} 1. Nc3 d5 {Bxf6 as after exf6! our bishops will dominate the board.  Don't be afraid to get an IQP structure as our bishop pair and active play are compensation for the structural weakness. White's main line d5 is met with} 2. Ne4 $1 {Bf4} e6 $1 {The point is to meet} 3. f3 {with a timely} Bd6 $1 {After the trade of the dark-squared bishops, we enjoy Benoni-like play with a ... b5 expansion.}) ({Finally, if White plays} 1. Nc3 {aiming for a Sicilian-like structure, we go for a central strategy with} d5 $1 {Remember to take back on f6 with the e-pawn, and in case of the rare} 2. e4 {to take on e4 with the knight! Once you learn these lines, you will actually enjoy facing this rare opening.}) *

