{The Torre Attack is best met with h6! If White goes for the trade with Bxf6 and an e4 / d4 center grab, we develop naturally with ... d6 , ... g6 , and ... Bg7 . Don't forget to get counterplay with ... b5 and keep in mind that two bishops will tear up the board once the game opens up. If White goes for a positional approach with Bh4 , we strike the center with c5! The ideas are similar to the London System. If possible, we trade the light-squared bishops with ... Ba6 , or if White stops this plan with Qe2 then we go for the fianchetto plan with ... Bb7 followed by ... d6 and a timely trade of the DSB with ... Nh5 ! Black eventually gets an extra central pawn and tries to prepare a long-term ... e5 break.} 1. Z0 *

[Event "?"]
