rong knight on e5 , and if Black is not careful, we can get under a strong attack with ... f4 , ... Qf3 , ... Qh3 etc. However, I will show you a cool regrouping that deals with this plan. The key is to win the e4 -outpost.}) 11... Rc8 {First we activate our rook and X-ray the c2 -pawn.} 12. f4 Ne7 {This is the key idea! The knight is heading to f5 , and the fight is revolving around the e4 -square now.} 13. g4 Ne4 {And Black takes over the game!} *

