{We meet the Colle-Zukertort with strong central play with ... c5 , ... Nc6 , & ... d5 . When White goes for the Colle Setup with c3 , we continue with natural developing moves Bd6 Nbd2 O-O . Remember to retreat the bishop to e7 after the eventual dxc5 & b4 from White in order to strike in the center with ... e5 ! If White goes for Colle-Zukertort b3 & Bb2 setup, we also fianchetto our bishop with ... b6 & ... Bb7 . Then we clarify the situation in the center with ... cxd4 and develop naturally with ... Bd6 & ... O-O .   Once you reach the classic tabiya after White's knight is on e5 , remember this plan: ... Rc8 , ... Ne7 & ... Nf5 ! often provoke g4 and get ready to sacrifice a pawn with a timely ... Ne4 ! jump!} 1. Z0 *

