{The Richter-Veresov Attack is easily parried with a quiet pawn move h6! If White takes with Bxf6 , remember to take back with the e-pawn exf6! and go for active piece play. Greek gift anyone? If White drops the bishop back with Bh4 then c5 gives us an easy plan. We will develop naturally ( ... Nc6 , ... cxd4 , ... Bf5 , ... e6 , etc.) and enjoy a nice middlegame structure as the knight on c3 is totally misplaced.} 1. Z0 *

