[PlyCount "28"]
[GameId "2176748630025299"]

1. c4 c5 2. g3 {With this move order White often tries to delay Nf3 , or play without Nf3 .} g6 {Our response is simple to continue with symmetry, but keep in the mind we like symmetry as long as White doesn't play Nf3 . Make sure that you don't accidentally meet Nf3 with ... Nf6 ? as this would ruin our entire setup!} 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. Nc3 Nc6 {For now, we still continue with symmetrical development. It's very important to keep full control over the d4 -outpost, thus we need to keep the knight on g8 . Now, White has to make a big decision here:} {Go for the main line with Nf3 or play a tricky waiting move a3!? or try to develop e3 and Nge2 . We will cover both 5. a3 !? and 5. e3 in this chapter.} 5. e3 {White wants to develop the knight with 6. Nge2 and castle next.} h5 {Remember this important idea! Whenever White is going for Nge2 plan we would love to get our pawn to h4 or provoke h4 from White.} 6. h4 {This is a typical knee-jerk reaction to ... h5 , but now the g4 & f5 squares are weakened.} Nh6 {This is the best development square for our knight. We don't block the bishop and take both g4 & f5 under control.} 7. Nge2 d6 {There's no hurry to play for ... Nf5 . As a matter of fact, I'd like to invite them to a cup of tea and to play their plan with ... d4 .} 8. d4 Bg4 {White is now faced with an unpleasant pin.} 9. f3 cxd4 {A nice intermezzo.} 10. exd4 (10. Nxd4 {is met with . We will play ... Nf5 next with huge pressure on White’s d4 -knight. Please note that both of White’s bishops are locked in.}) 10... Bd7 {Black's bishop sortie to g4 and back induced f3 . Now you can see that White's bishop on g2 is locked.} 11. O-O {This logical move turns out to be a mistake already!} Nf5 {We force White to advance the pawn.} 12. d5 Ne5 {Black's knights dominate the board. The engine already gives Black almost -2 advantage! Let me know what happens if White tries to defend c4 -pawn.} 13. b3 a6 {The idea is to play for ... b5} 14. a4 O-O {Black is much better as White is totally paralyzed. We will play ... Rb8 and ... b5 next and take over the queenside.} *

