1. c4 c5 2. g3 {With this move order White often tries to delay Nf3 , or play without Nf3 .} g6 {Our response is simple to continue with symmetry, but keep in the mind we like symmetry as long as White doesn't play Nf3 . Make sure that you don't accidentally meet Nf3 with ... Nf6 ? as this would ruin our entire setup!} 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. Nc3 Nc6 {For now, we still continue with symmetrical development. It's very important to keep full control over the d4 -outpost, thus we need to keep the knight on g8 . Now, White has to make a big decision here:} {Go for the main line with Nf3 or play a tricky waiting move a3!? or try to develop e3 and Nge2 . We will cover both 5. a3 !? and 5. e3 in this chapter.} 5. e3 {White wants to develop the knight with 6. Nge2 and castle next.} h5 {Remember this important idea! Whenever White is going for Nge2 plan we would love to get our pawn to h4 or provoke h4 from White.} 6. h3 {This quiet move is probably White's best. Now they would meet ... h4 with g4 ! So, we need to delay this push by one more move.} d6 7. Nge2 h4 {This is the sharpest continuation, but Black can also play the calm ... e5 and ... Nge7 plan.} 8. g4 f5 {The point. We still insist of breaking open White's kingside.} 9. gxf5 Bxf5 {Our bishop is developed with a tempo.} 10. d4 cxd4 {We don't mind giving White the center for now as the d4 -pawn will be weak.} 11. exd4 Qd7 {The key move! We create a battery on h3 -pawn, stopping White from castling short. At the same time, we entertain the idea of castling long in some lines!} 12. Be3 Nf6 13. Qd2 {White is preparing long castle, but now runs into problems.} Nb4 {A deadly move. White is now on the verge of collapse due to many threats of ... Nd3 + or ... Nc2 +.} 14. Ne4 {White uses tactics to stay alive, but Black is better still.} a5 {The strongest! Of course, you can take on e4 as well.} 15. Nxf6+ Bxf6 16. Kf1 {A sad move to make as White had to stop knight jumps.} O-O {Black finishes development and clearly stands better. We will have all the fun attacking White's poor king on f1 .} *

