[Black "Conclusion: 2.g3 Symmetrical English"]
[Result "*"]
[PlyCount "1"]
[GameId "2176748630025315"]

{If White delays Nf3 , they typically go for the early a3 / b4 plan or the central e3 , Nge2 , & d4 setup. In the first case, make sure to remember the simple setup based on a3 b6! Black will fianchetto the bishop and neutralize White on the long diagonal.  Don't forget about the cool idea of b4 Bb7 Rb1 Bxc3! We trade our DSB for the knight and double White's pawns, similar to the Nimzo. This gives Black excellent long-term chances and we often take over the game, especially after the trade of the light-squared bishops. In case White goes for e3 , we answer with Harry the h-pawn push h5! This often leads to fun and exciting chess, especially if White allows Nge2 h4! where we dominate on the kingside.  White's best is h3 , but even there, we seek counterplay with ... d6 & ... h4 in order to meet g4 with ... f5 ! with a complex middlegame and good chances to outplay our opponent.} 1. Z0 *

