ieces.} 12. Nxg6 ({The only move to stay alive. A bishop retreat such as} 12. Bd2 {loses after a simple tactic} Rxh4 13. gxh4 Qg4+ {with mate.}) 12... fxg5 13. Nxh8 Bxh8 {The dust has settled. We have 2 minor pieces for the rook and two pawns. However, it's clear that our minor pieces are dominant in this middlegame since White's rooks don't have any open files to work with.   We will play ... O-O-O next with a big attack.} *

