 but it gives White an opportunity to defend with} 12. Bg2 $1) 12. Bg2 Rxh3 13. Bxh3 (13. hxg3 {transposes to the main line, see 12.hxg3.}) 13... gxf2+ (13... Qxh3 {also wins}) 14. Kxf2 Qxh3 {White's king is too exposed to many of our threats such as ... Qxh2 + or ... Nf6 and ... Ng4 . White is lost here, and the engine confirms with -3 eval.} *

