[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "16) English Opening: Early Fianchetto"]
[Black "Conclusion: 2.Nf3 Symmetrical English"]
[Result "*"]
[PlyCount "1"]
[GameId "2176748630090866"]

{If White develops their knight to f3 , remember our key setup: develop the bishop to f5 with Bf5 and if White goes for the standard d3 we play Qd7 in order to trade the light square bishops with …Bh3! If White prepares for it with Re1 now the key idea is to insert Bh3 and after Bh1 h5! Remember Harry the h-pawn storm with a big attack. However, if White stops our idea with Bf5 h3 then we follow Dubov’s path with Qc8 and finish development with …Nf6 & ... O-O . Black’s ideas involve the Dragon tail swing with …a6 & ... b5 and central play like in the game Svidler-Dubov.} 1. Z0 *

