1. c4 c5 2. Nf3 {White has many different move orders, but they more or less reach the key position we see on move 6.} ({White can start with} 2. Nf3 {c5 and then play c4 or .}) ({White can start with c4 c5} 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. Nc3 Nc6 {and now play Nf3 , etc.}) 2... g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e3 {White aims to play for d4 push, so we need to prepare with a classic ... d5 counter. Thus we play ... Nf6 !} Nf6 {We are ready to meet d4 with cxd4 and ... d5 !} 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 {This is a harmless idea as White will be down a tempo vs the regular Maroczy Bind.} O-O 7. e4 {White gets the bind but a tempo down!} e6 {The simplest, we will play for ... d5 next.} 8. Be2 d5 {This move forces massive liquidation in the center with an easy game.} *

