1. c4 c5 2. Nf3 {White has many different move orders, but they more or less reach the key position we see on move 6.} ({White can start with} 2. Nf3 {c5 and then play c4 or .}) ({White can start with c4 c5} 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. Nc3 Nc6 {and now play Nf3 , etc.}) 2... g6 3. d4 {White tries to establish the central control with the knight on d4 right away.} cxd4 4. Nxd4 {White is about to play e4 and get the classic Maroczy Bind. Remember, we have to stop it!} Nf6 {Stopping e4 . Here White can renew the threat of e4 with logical 5. Nc3 or go back to slow English approach with 5. g3} 5. g3 {White goes for the slow English approach of developing the bishop first. Here, I have a nice surprise for our opponent.} h5 {This is a very rare move with only a handful of games in the DB, but it scores really well. White is now a bit uncomfortable facing ... h4 and need to decide whether to allow it with Bg2 or stop it with h4 or h3 moves.} 6. Bg2 {White ignores our threats and goes for rapid development.} h4 {We execute our Harry the h-pawn march. It is seen in many instances of our repertoire. Remember, I proposed this idea vs the e3 , Nge2 setup. It's also a common idea against the main line where we play with a ... Bf5 & ... Qd7 battery.} 7. Nc3 Bg7 (7... Nc6 {would likely transpose after} 8. O-O Bg7 {.}) 8. Bg5 {White puts pressure on our h-pawn, but it wants to go to h3 anyways.} h3 {A nice tempo on the bishop.} 9. Bf3 Nc6 10. O-O {Here Black has many plans that lead to good play, let me share with you a possible line.} Qa5 {We put pressure on g5 -bishop. White has to be careful to avoid tactical pitfalls now.} 11. Be3 (11. Qd2 $2 {loses to} Nxd4 {while Ndb5? loses to a6!}) 11... Ne5 {A nice tempo on f3 bishop and c4 -pawn.} 12. Qb3 O-O (12... Nxf3+ {is fine as well if you are a fan of the bishop pair.}) 13. Bh1 d6 {We've reached a great version of g3 line with a pawn on g3 and our powerful knight on e5 . White obviously can't take on b7 due to ... Rab8 . We will play ... Rb8 next and prepare counterplay on the queenside.} *

