{When White plays for an early Nc3 to prepare e4 , we must answer with d5! Remember, this is the only way to prevent the classic Maroczy Bind! Often the game enters symmetrical positions where we lose the right to castle. However, don't worry as our king is well-placed in the center and with natural development, Black gets easy game.  Remember the cool h5! idea to take advantage of well-placed rook on h8 . If White goes for slow English plan with g3 then we have a surprise for them with h5! Harry the h-pawn creates havoc on the kingside. White either gets under a big attack or has to make concessions on the kingside such as giving up the g4 -outpost with h4 .} 1. Z0 *

