{The Botvinnik English is best met with an early 5... a6 ! and  and b5! pawn sacrifice. We get excellent compensation and deny White the easy setup. In case White meets a6! with a4 , we go for the normal Dragon setup and try to win the dark squares with a thematic 7... Bg4 ! & ... Bxf3 idea. Remember, that controlling the dark squares and specifically the d4 -outpost is vital for Black.} 1. Z0 *

