1. Nf3 {In this chapter we will cover the Reti opening where White goes for the immediate kingside fianchetto with 2. g3 , 3. Bg2 , and 4. O-O .} c5 2. g3 ({After} 2. c4 g6 {we transpose to the English lines.}) 2... g6 {We also fianchetto our bishop.} 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O Nc6 5. d3 {White still has a choice to go for 6. e4 or 6. c4 plans.} d6 {We also achieved our Dragon setup and wait for White to show us their plan.} 6. e4 {This approach takes the game into the King's Indian Attack (KIA) or the Closed Sicilian territory. If you already studied my HAD course, you know what to do: we finish development with ... Nf6 & ... O-O and start playing on the queenside with ... Rb8 and ... b5 . Remember the basic rule of thumb when coming up with a plan: The Dragon swings with his tail!} Nf6 {We continue to develop the kingside. White typically fights for the center with c3 , Re1 & d4 or goes 7. Nbd2 .} 7. c3 {White aims to play 8.Re1 & d4 next.} O-O 8. Re1 {White is ready to play for d4 .} e5 {An important idea to remember! We need to be aware of White's plan and prepare for it.} ({Please note that} 8... Rb8 {is still playable, but allows .}) 9. a3 {This unusual pawn move is part of White's plan to play for b4 next.} b5 {We take free space on the queenside. Notice that we didn't have to spend a tempo on ... Rb8 .} 10. h3 ({This is the most common move and played by a strong Egyptian GM Bassem Amin, who's also a medical doctor!} 10. b4 {is met with} a5 $1 {anyway.}) 10... a5 {We continue grabbing more space.} 11. a4 {White hopes to establish a strong outpost on c4 .} b4 {I believe our space advantage is more valuable than the c4 -outpost.} 12. Nbd2 h6 {A useful prophylactic move, preparing ... Be6 .} 13. Nc4 Be6 {There's only one game in the DB where this complex position was reached. I believe Black's space advantage on the queenside should give us a small edge, but the big fight is still ahead.} 14. Kh2 Kh7 15. Be3 Qc7 {We connect the rooks.} 16. Nfd2 Nd7 {We prepare ... f5 !} 17. Qc2 f5 {Black is now taking over the kingside, ... f4 being a big threat. The engine also loves Black, giving us around a -1 edge.} *

