{White's Reti setup based on 1.Nf3 , 2.g3 , 3.Bg2 , and 4.O-O is met with our standard reaction to the English with 1...c5 , 2...g6 , 3...Bg7 , and .  If after d3 d6 White goes for symmetry with c4 , we react with e6 , ... Nge7 followed by a double fianchetto. If White goes for e4 , we go for a standard queenside expansion idea with ... b5 . Remember to meet the c3 & Re1 plan with ... e5 ! Black will still expand on the queenside with a good game.} 1. Z0 *

