1. Nf3 c5 2. b3 {This combo of Nf3 & b3 is a aimed to stop our plan of ... g6 . However, I will show you a cool idea where we still get to fianchetto our bishop.} Nc6 3. Bb2 Nf6 {We don't mind the trade on f6 as it would give us two powerful bishops.} 4. g3 {White goes for the double fianchetto, but gives us central control.} d5 {We grab the center of course! Please note that we still don't mind the trade on f6 , as we will capture ... exf6 .} 5. Bg2 Qc7 {I like this quiet queen move, preparing a center push ... e5 .} 6. d4 cxd4 7. Nxd4 e5 {We still control the center.} 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. O-O h5 {Please note that the stable center allows us to launch a pawn storm right away. We will meet c4 with ... d4 and continue with ... h4 , creating a powerful attack.} *

