{Our setup for this system looks like, Nf3 c5 b3 Nc6 .  Remember, to meet Bb2 with Nf6! in order to play ... g6 and fianchetto our DSB. We are never worried about White taking on f6 as after ... exf6 ! (similar to the Trompowsky) our bishops will rule the board. If White goes for the tame setup with e3 g6 d4 remember to trade on d4 . If they take with a pawn, we will play ... d5 ! and block off the b2 -bishop, and if they can with the knight, we finish development of the kingside, take on d4 and play for the center with ... d5 , ... Qd6 & ... e5 !} 1. Z0 *

