1. h3 {This is called the Clemenz Opening. I guess White is trying to play the improved Grob with 2. g4 next. The most important part now is... to allow it, of course!} Nf6 {We give White a chance to play a sensible move like d4 next, which would lead to normal openings up a tempo for us. It's rare that h3 is a useful move in closed openings.} 2. g4 {White plays the improved Grob!} d5 ({We can also play} 2... e5 {, but this is simple and strong: we put our pawn in the center.}) 3. g5 {Hikaru tried this in blitz, but White gets overextended.} Nfd7 (3... Nh5 {is not bad either.}) 4. Bg2 Nb6 {Hikaru's GM opponent played a solid 4... c6 , but this is more ambitious!} 5. d3 e5 {We grab the center.} 6. a4 a5 {We are not giving White an inch of space!} 7. b3 Nc6 8. h4 Be6 {Now, we have a simple plan of ... Qd7 and castle long. White has a bad version of the Hippo.} 9. Bb2 Qd7 10. e3 O-O-O 11. Ne2 h6 {Black is enjoying a large advantage already. The engine gives us a winning -2.6 edge!} *

