1. c3 {This is not a serious opening as it will likely transpose to the London or to the Colle Openings.} Nf6 2. d4 e6 3. Bg5 {This is the most common move, White is playing like the Torre Attack but without the inclusion of Nf3 .} (3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 Be7 {this transposes to the London System .}) 3... c5 {Our standard reaction against the London/Torre.} 4. e3 h6 {Always a useful move, asking the bishop a question.} 5. Bh4 Qb6 {Let's take advantage of White's early bishop sortie and attack b2 .} ({Black can of course play normally with} 5... Be7 {with similar play as in our Torre Attack chapter.}) 6. Qc1 {The queen is a bit misplaced on the c-file.} Nc6 7. Nf3 d5 {Simple chess, we grab more central space.} 8. Bd3 Ne4 9. Nbd2 g5 10. Bg3 Nxg3 11. hxg3 g4 12. Nh4 h5 {White's knight on h4 is totally out of the game. Black is clearly better due to the bishop pair and a nice space advantage.} *

