1. c3 {This is not a serious opening as it will likely transpose to the London or to the Colle Openings.} Nf6 2. d4 e6 3. Bg5 {This is the most common move, White is playing like the Torre Attack but without the inclusion of Nf3 .} (3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 Be7 {this transposes to the London System .}) 3... c5 {Our standard reaction against the London/Torre.} 4. e3 h6 {Always a useful move, asking the bishop a question.} 5. Bh4 Qb6 {Let's take advantage of White's early bishop sortie and attack b2 .} ({Black can of course play normally with} 5... Be7 {with similar play as in our Torre Attack chapter.}) 6. b3 {This is perhaps the worst option as it weakens c3 -pawn.} Nc6 7. Nf3 cxd4 8. exd4 g5 9. Bg3 Ne4 {We will take on g3 next and our bishops will dominate the middlegame.} *

