1. g4 {The Grob Attack! It was invented by the Swiss International Master Henri Grob (1904–1974). Later, it was picked up by the English International Master Michael Basman with some success.   These days it's known to be quite unsound. White is daring Black: either refute the opening or lose trying and make one for the lolz! Now that you bought my course, hopefully moves such as 1. g4 will bring a smile to your face as I present you the simple refutation.} d5 {Simple chess! Black takes control over the center and attacks the g4 -pawn.} 2. Bg2 {White gambits the g4 -pawn, hoping for rapid development and quick use of the long a8 - h1 diagonal.} (2. f3 $2 {this was seen at GM level and White lost the game in 5 moves, after} e5 3. d3 Qh4+ 4. Kd2 h5 5. h3 hxg4 {and Black resigned in Hou Yifan -Lalith, B Caleta, 2017.  You may wonder, did the former Women's World Champion have a bad day? The answer is actually quite simple: this is her protest game against the organizers after she was paired in 7 out of 9 games vs women in a big open tournament with lots of men! An interesting way to get your message across...}) (2. h3 {just gives away all central control} e5 {and Black will have all the fun with two central pawns.}) 2... Bxg4 {Of course, we take the free pawn!} 3. c4 {The point. Now that the bishop is lured away from c8 , you can see that both b7 & d5 are quite weak.} c6 {Simple chess. Black just supports the key d5 -pawn.} 4. Qb3 {Played by GMs Hikaru Nakamura vs Mamedyarov.} Nf6 {Black happily sacrifices the b7 -pawn for initiative.} (4... e6 $1 5. Qxb7 Nd7 {is also quite strong.}) 5. cxd5 ({Hikaru's choice in a Titled Tuesday blitz game.} 5. Nc3 e6 6. cxd5 cxd5 7. Qxb7 Nbd7 {transposes to 5. cxd5 .}) 5... cxd5 6. Qxb7 {The insertion of cxd5 doesn't help White much, Black is still better.} Nbd7 {A simple developing move, White's queen is a bit stranded now.} 7. Nc3 {The most common move in DB.} e6 {Black just continues development. White's queen is a bit stranded on b7 .} (7... Rb8 $1 {is strong as well}) 8. Nb5 {Trying to be active, with a simple threat of Nc7 +} Rc8 {Black activates the rook while stopping the fork.} 9. Qxa7 Bc5 10. Qa4 O-O {Black is much better due to a huge lead in development.} *

