1. b3 {This is the Larsen's Opening where White tries to delay the fight for the center and fianchetto the dark-squared bishop. I recommend an idea based on the central strategy 1... e5 but with a twist: we plan to sacrifice our central pawn for the bishop pair later.} e5 {We fight for the center from move one!} 2. Bb2 Nc6 {We develop our knight and defend the pawn, aiming to take over the center with ... d5 next. Here, White has two approaches:} ({e3 with the idea to meet} 2... d5 {with a Bb5 pin. This is the main line.}) {Or, c4 trying to get the game into English territory.} 3. e3 {This is the main line. White wants to meet d5 with .} d5 {We grab the full control of the center.} 4. Bb5 {White creates a direct threat of Bxe5 , using the pin tactic.} Nge7 ({We 'fall' for White's trap! This idea was a shocking revelation to me a few years ago, when I started working with neural network engine, Leela. Now, it's a known concept and just as popular as the main line} 4... Bd6 {.}) 5. Bxe5 {White takes our gift.} a6 {The point! Now, White has to part with the bishop pair.} 6. Bxc6+ Nxc6 {This is an interesting position. We gave up a central pawn, but have the two bishops and a serious lead in development. If you love initiative, you will enjoy playing this line.} 7. Bg3 {This is the best move, but it's so counter-intuitive that only 10% of players make it in blitz! Normally, 7.Bb2 is played on autopilot.} ({However, as you will see} 7. Bb2 {is bad due to} Qg5 $1) 7... h5 {A useful expansion and a tempo move. Now, White has to deal with ... h4 .} 8. h3 {This was played by GM Hikaru Nakamura in blitz, but he got into a lot of trouble.} h4 9. Bh2 Qg5 ({Now White has to make a concession as Qf3 is met with} 9... Nb4 $1) 10. Kf1 Bf5 {Black just continues development and plans to castle long. Remember, our initiative is long-term, so we can take our time to finish development.} 11. Nf3 (11. Bxc7 {is losing even more time and after} Rc8 {our advantage only keeps on growing.}) 11... Qf6 ({GM Hikaru faced} 11... Qg6 {in a blitz game, but this is even stronger.}) 12. Nc3 O-O-O 13. Bf4 d4 {Black is enjoying the initiative and aims to blow up the game even more.} 14. Bg5 {The tactics work in our favor after this.} Qg6 15. Bxd8 Bxc2 16. Qc1 dxc3 {This is a big edge for us!} *

