1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Qe7 5. g3 Nc6 6. Bg2 Bxd2+ 7. Nbxd2 O-O 8. O-O d6 9. Nb3 {An unsual square for the knight. Now, Black gets to execute the main idea with ease.} e5 10. d5 Nb8 11. Qc2 b6 {Securing the c5 -outpost.} 12. e4 a5 13. Nfd2 Na6 14. Nc1 Nc5 15. Ne2 Bd7 16. Nc3 Rfb8 {Hinting at ... b5} 17. Rfe1 h6 18. Bf1 Nh7 19. Qd1 Rf8 {I change my mind and go for the ... f5 pawn break.} 20. Nf3 Ng5 21. Nxg5 Qxg5 22. Qc1 Qg6 23. Qe3 f5 24. exf5 Bxf5 {Black has achieved all the strategic goals of the opening. I have the c5 -outpost and beautiful pressure on the f-file.} 25. Bg2 Rf7 26. Ne4 Nxe4 27. Bxe4 Raf8 28. Bxf5 Rxf5 29. Re2 Rf3 30. Qd2 h5 {Now, the major pieces and the h-pawn work together to attack White's king.} 31. Qc2 Qg4 32. Rf1 R8f4 33. b3 h4 34. Rfe1 hxg3 35. fxg3 Rxg3+ 36. Rg2 (36. hxg3 Qxg3+ {wins}) 36... Rxg2+ 37. Qxg2 Qf5 {White flagged in a losing position.} (37... Qf5 38. Kh1 Rf2 {wins}) *

